Subject: Re: [T2] Suggestion for removing broken cylinder stud

On Tue, 11 Mar 2003, Jeff Strickrott wrote:

> Any suggestion on a removal procedure I can do at home? Or is it off to
> the machine shop for some heat treatment and careful drilling/tapping. I
> thought I might use some liquid nitrogen to cool down the case to make
> the threads looser. Think this will work?

No, the stud has to be cooled and the case warmed, which is really hard
with the stud broken off flush.  I'd take it to a machine shop at this
point unless you're _really_ good with a drill.  The machinist will be
much happier to see the case without a broken-off drill or EZ-out in the
hole.

George Lyle
